    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Visual works, particularly works of art or high craft, that are created from textile materials, which are plant, animal, and synthetic fibers used in weaving, sewing, knitting, felting, knotting, etc. Textile art uses exclusively, or nearly exclusively, textiles as both the support and media, if any media are applied. Embroidery is a textile art, because the support is textile and also the material used to create the design is a textile. However, in another example, oil paintings are generally painted on canvas, which is a textile material: but oil paintings are not considered textile art because the medium is paint. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000011141/Fleming and Honour, Dictionary of the Decorative Arts (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beeldmateriaal gemaakt uit textielmaterialen: plantaardige, dierlijke en synthetische vezels gebruikt voor weven, naaien, breien, vervilten, knopen, etc. Textielkunst maakt uitsluitend of bijna uitsluitend gebruik van textiel, zowel voor de drager als voor de media, als er media worden toegepast. Borduurwerk is een vorm van textielkunst, omdat de drager van textiel is en ook het materiaal waarmee het ontwerp wordt gemaakt. Olieverfschilderingen daarentegen worden weliswaar meestal op doek geschilderd, dat een textielmateriaal is, maar worden niet als textielkunst beschouwd omdat het medium verf is.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Obras visuais, especialmente obras de arte ou artesanato, criadas a partir de materiais têxteis, que são plantas, animais e fibras sintéticas usadas em tecelagem, costura, tricô, feltragem, atadura, etc. A arte têxtil usa exclusivamente, ou quase exclusivamente, têxteis como suporte e mídia, se alguma mídia for aplicada. O bordado é uma arte têxtil, porque o suporte é têxtil e também o material usado para criar o design é um têxtil. No entanto, em outro exemplo, as pinturas a óleo geralmente são pintadas em tela, que é um material têxtil: mas as pinturas a óleo não são consideradas arte têxtil porque o meio é tinta</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
